On 11/8/05, Mike Benthin <benthin(-at-)prodigy.net> wrote:
>
> In my estimation, owner-made parcel trays made of solid shelving are
> knee busters waiting to happen if one has a front end collision.



I agree. The design I have in mind is going to be framed with plywood with
the low sections 1"x1" patterned after my table:
http://www.donimages.com/73westy/pics/table08.jpg. The edges will be wavy so
there will be thicker sections, but the thin sections should be enough to
crumble under impact, but hold under normal use..

The bottom will be a wicker matting.






